'''格拉斯哥語'''，又稱'''格拉斯哥方言'''，是[[英國|英國]][[蘇格蘭|蘇格蘭]][[格拉斯哥|格拉斯哥]]通行的一種[[蘇格蘭方言|蘇格蘭方言]]。受到中部蘇格蘭語，高地英語以及[[愛爾蘭英語|愛爾蘭英語]]的影響，<ref>{{Citation | last = Menzies | first = Janet | title = An Investigation of Attitudes to Scots | url = http://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/STELLA/STARN/lang/MENZIES/menzie1.htm | journal = Scottish Language | volume = 10 | pages = 30–46 | year = 1991 | accessdate = 2014-11-05 | archive-date = 2020-11-11 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201111215204/https://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/STELLA/STARN/lang/MENZIES/menzie1.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref> 肇因19世紀末至20世紀初，大量移居格拉斯哥市區的高地蘇格蘭人及愛爾蘭人奠定。<ref>{{cite book|last=Fraser|first=W. Hamish |author2=Thomas Martin Devine |author3=Gordon Jackson |author4=Irene Maver  | title=Glasgow: Volume II: 1830-1912|publisher=Manchester University Press| year=1997|pages=149–150|isbn=978-0-7190-3692-7 }}</ref>該方言廣泛應用於格拉斯哥地區，部分當地媒體以及相關出版物。隨時代變遷，格拉斯哥語也發展和完善關於當地著名人物和建築的書面描述。

==式微==
部分統計證實，年輕族群以及傳統格拉斯哥語使用族群（多為[[工薪階層|工薪階層]]）在日常生活中已經越來越多的採用倫敦發音和倫敦詞彙，<ref>[http://www.esrcsocietytoday.ac.uk/ESRCInfoCentre/ViewAwardPage.aspx?AwardId=1892 Is TV a contributory factor in accent change in adolescents?] {{webarchive|url=http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20091213155241/http://www.esrcsocietytoday.ac.uk/ESRCInfoCentre/ViewAwardPage.aspx?AwardId=1892 |date=2009-12-13 }} - ESRC Society Today</ref> 傳統格拉斯哥語詞彙及語法岌岌可危。<ref>[http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/smgpubs/access/571152461.html?did=571152461&FMT=ABS&FMTS=FT&date=Mar%2B4,%2B2004&author=&desc=Cockney%2Bcreep%2Bputs%2Bpaid%2Bto%2Bthe%2Bpatter Cockney creep puts paid to the patter] {{Wayback|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/smgpubs/access/571152461.html?did=571152461&FMT=ABS&FMTS=FT&date=Mar%2B4,%2B2004&author=&desc=Cockney%2Bcreep%2Bputs%2Bpaid%2Bto%2Bthe%2Bpatter |date=20130316042955 }} - Evening Times</ref> 例如輔音/θ/越來越傾向於倫敦發音（以/f/和/v/代替齒摩擦音），以及部分詞彙中[[齒齦顫音|齒齦顫音]]/r/的弱化。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/journal/117980167/abstract?CRETRY=1&SRETRY=0 |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2014-11-05 |archive-date=2013-01-05 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130105064601/http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/journal/117980167/abstract?CRETRY=1&SRETRY=0 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> 但齒齦顫音的弱化也可能咎于其他地區蘇格蘭人的湧入（例如中部城市帶的蘇格蘭人），不一定是受到[[英語|英語]]的影響。<ref>Speitel, H. H. & Johnston, P. (1983). ESRC End of Grant Report “A Sociolinguistic Investigation of Edinburgh Speech.”</ref> 統計顯示格拉斯哥語的式微很大程度上是由於[[大眾傳媒|大眾傳媒]]大部分使用倫敦及英格蘭東南部發音所致。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/3531075.stm |title=Soaps may be washing out accent - BBC Scotland |access-date=2014-11-05 |archive-date=2017-08-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170801043934/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/3531075.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>[http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/uk/article1036798.ece 'We fink, so we are from Glasgow'] {{Wayback|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/uk/article1036798.ece |date=20110814141539 }} - Times Online</ref><ref>[http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_/ai_n16503073 Scots kids rabbitin' like Cockneys] {{Wayback|url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_/ai_n16503073 |date=20151016062946 }} - Sunday Herald</ref><ref>[http://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/sesll/EngLang/phonetics/index.html - Faculty of Arts, University of Glasgow] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080530235558/http://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/sesll/EngLang/phonetics/index.html |date=2008-05-30 }}</ref>

